subject: Soccer
lead_paragraph: The French national team was humbled, 3-1, by Austria as Europe’s big guns began their 2010 World Cup qualifying campaigns. It proved to be the only major upset on a day that Italy, the defending champion, snatched a 2-1 stoppage-time victory in Cyprus; the European champion Spain edged Bosnia, 1-0; Germany crushed Liechtenstein, 6-0; and the English team was booed before beating Andorra, 2-0.
